Problem:
Given the root of a binary tree, your task is to find the maximum path sum. 
The path may start and end at any node in the tree.

Code:
class Solution {
    int findMaxSum(Node root) {
     
        if(root == null) return 0;
        
        
        int[] sum = new int[1];
        sum[0] = Integer.MIN_VALUE;
        
        f(root, sum);
        
        return sum[0];
    }
    
    private int f(Node root, int[] sum) {
        
        if(root == null) return 0;
        
        int leftSum = f(root.left, sum);
        int rightSum = f(root.right, sum);
        
        if(leftSum < 0) leftSum = 0;
        if(rightSum < 0) rightSum = 0;
        
        int total = leftSum + rightSum + root.data;
        
        sum[0] = Math.max(total, sum[0]);
        
        return Math.max(leftSum, rightSum) + root.data;
    }
}